## Confidence Scoring Requirements (MANDATORY — AIR-Q07, AIR-Q08)

Every extracted item MUST include a `confidence_score` in [0.0, 1.0]:

| Score range | Meaning | System action |
|-------------|---------|---------------|
| 0.95 – 1.00 | Value clearly and unambiguously stated | Auto-approved |
| 0.80 – 0.94 | Stated but minor interpretation needed | Auto-approved |
| 0.60 – 0.79 | Partially stated or inferred | **Flagged for manual review** |
| 0.00 – 0.59 | Guessed or highly ambiguous | **Flagged for manual review** |
| null        | Confidence genuinely unassessable | **Flagged for mandatory review** |

Items with confidence below 0.80 OR null will appear in the staff manual review queue.
Do NOT omit or round confidence to avoid flagging. Be calibrated and honest.

## Extraction Requirements

Extract ALL of the following entity types present in the document.
For each item include all fields plus `confidence_score`, `source_reference`, `page_number`,
and `extraction_region`.

### Medications
- drug_name (required)
- dosage
- frequency
- route
- prescribing_physician
- prescription_date (ISO-8601 YYYY-MM-DD; use YYYY-MM if day unknown; YYYY if only year known)
- confidence_score (required)
- source_reference: the exact text snippet the value was extracted from (≤ 200 chars)
- page_number (integer; 1 if unknown)
- extraction_region (e.g. "medication table row 2")

### Diagnoses
- condition_name (required)
- icd_code
- diagnosis_date (ISO-8601 YYYY-MM-DD; use partial format if day/month unknown)
- treating_provider
- status (active | resolved | chronic)
- confidence_score (required)
- source_reference
- page_number
- extraction_region

### Procedures
- procedure_name (required)
- procedure_date (ISO-8601 YYYY-MM-DD; use partial format if incomplete)
- performing_physician
- facility
- cpt_code
- confidence_score (required)
- source_reference
- page_number
- extraction_region

### Allergies
- allergen (required)
- reaction_type
- severity (mild | moderate | severe | life-threatening)
- onset_date (ISO-8601; partial allowed)
- status (active | inactive)
- confidence_score (required)
- source_reference
- page_number
- extraction_region

## Partial Date Handling (Edge Case)

When a date is present but incomplete:
- Year + month only (e.g. "March 2024") → use "2024-03" (YYYY-MM format).
- Year only (e.g. "2024") → use "2024" (YYYY format).
- Do NOT fabricate a full date. Use the partial form and set confidence proportionally lower.

## Output Rules

- Call `extract_with_confidence` exactly once.
- Include `extraction_outcome`: one of ["extracted", "no-data-extracted", "unsupported-language"].
- Include `overall_confidence`: aggregate confidence score [0.0, 1.0] for the whole extraction.
- Omit fields that are genuinely absent (do not use placeholder strings like "N/A").
- Never include patient names, contact info, or SSN in any field value — these are PII.
- Your output is for clinical staff review; accuracy matters more than completeness.
